<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 3:35AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms with Heavy Rain...
At 330 AM CDT...Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with heavy
rain moving across the area. The storms are producing torrential
rainfall with around an inch in less than an hour. This will
likely result in minor flooding of low lying or poorly drained
areas, especially in locations which saw significant rainfall over
the past 24 hours.
If driving early this morning, please take it slow with the wet
roadways and reduced visibilities. Never drive into areas where
water covers the road!</description>
